The need for speed The Run is being fought all over America.
Revision
Initially, a race without problems is transformed due to a set of stupid mistakes of people who have nothing to do with a routine morning shift at work.
It fulfills to some extent everyone’s ambition but it serves no purpose if no one wants to do something more.
The new subtitled part The Run produced great expectations before its release.
He promised to take a new direction with the already aged Need for Speed racing series and to come out some sort of game from playable games that wouldn’t just count on points.
So we were curious as to how the added passages will be during which the main hero gets out of his car and does what he wants.
As is already done in the NFS series, the result is completely different from what was expected.
These are potentially arcade racing games but the set pulls down due to some useless mistakes that have already existed for several years.
These are not really mistakes, but rather the expression of an incomprehensible failure on the part of developers.
The adventure starts very well.
You are caught in the adventure whose main hero Jack has character problems and to solve them starts to take part in illegal races across America.
You sit behind the wheel on the west coast in San Francisco and your mission is to arrive first in New York.
The idea has interesting elements.
The route is divided into ten stages and then in more than 50 races.
As a result, each race takes place on a different route and the planned steps in different environments that are quite different from each other and are interesting.
The player does not have the feeling for a single moment that the game offers him something identical.
Some environments are super nice even though the graphical technical level is of the same type as the previous series.
This is not the end of the world.
But driving through the desert, in autumn landscapes or in high snowy mountains is very pleasant visually.
In addition, the tests are supplemented from time to time with an atypical element.
For example, in the desert you find yourself in a sandstorm that significantly decreases your visibility.
Then in the mountains you have to be careful that an avalanche does not fall on you.
Apart from this, the different races are well arranged behind each other.
There is only a small number, but that is enough.
There are moments when you try to exceed the required number of opponents (as in a classic race) then you run against the clock (classical duel with the timer) and then again you expect another duel with an opponent.
From time to time you also have the police who enter the game and who tries to make the situation difficult for you.
The new features are off-road crossings.
It is rather an interactive animation when most of the time Jack escapes in front of someone and you have to help him by tapping the right button at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
What is surprising is that there are fewer moments of this type than you expect (to be concrete there are only three).
As a result, this is a good thing because this element is not likely to interfere and is placed, in the context described above, in the elements that enhance the game.
The driving model is in the tradition of previous games.
This means that there is nothing extraordinary at the moment, but it cannot be said to be negative.
As far as realistic simulation is concerned, you will have to go elsewhere.
But although one can find better in the competition the driving model goes very well with the type of design of the races.
So everything is okay.
Problems begin to appear after a while.
Unlike the driving model, the collision model is not yet fully developed.
We do not expect from this game a complicated deformation and collisions, but when you do not have, during a collision with any object, the slightest idea of how your car behaves, so it is not completely good.
During tight overtakings you sometimes touch each other slightly but otherwise your self part in crazy turns.
Or it is found in ants.
Thanks to the reboot system this is not really a problem but it really annoys you.
The restart is done so that when you have broken the figure or you have come out in the setting the game takes you back to the moment of the last point on the route.
But you only have 5 restarts.
When you have used the 5 restarts you need to restart the game from the beginning.
So it’s more a tool, in case something doesn’t happen as it should, than something you can really count on.
Sometimes the restarts do not help and you need to find the solution by remembering the track in question.
The great hic of this game is that the same actions are found in the same places.
For example, there are some twists that you have to go through in a certain way otherwise it does not happen.
Otherwise you meet in a given place "civil" vehicles always in the same configuration as you arrived first, fifth, 5 seconds in advance or a minute late.
What gets angry are situations when you see easily pass the opponent between two cars coming in the opposite direction and when you arrive, you either have to set aside and turn them around or brake them.
It doesn’t matter if you go ahead of him because it’s “calculated” in such a way that for the given situation it always happens very close to your nose.
Opponents have other advantages.
During all the time in the game, you arrive in some places, again without worrying about time, and you always have the same opponent who precedes you in the same place.
This annoys the most at the end of the game when you ride on a long bridge in the opposite direction.
The opponent must pass in front of you at all costs.
When it passes in front of you it hides the view of other vehicles in the opposite direction and you come into collision a lot of times.
One can understand that the purpose of this game is to do something captivating and full of adrenaline, but it is clear that you get bored quickly.
And it’s a shame because through a simple driving model the game is interesting and places with so much action that you don’t have time to follow everything that happens.
And it doesn’t matter if it’s because of the concept of 50 unique itineraries, that the order of the races is such that there’s no chance of getting bored or anything else.
The original idea is to change the car during the races.
You need to pay attention to gas pumps on the routes as you can change cars there however most of the time the one you have is enough.
The cars are divided into three categories.
Sports cars are ideal for cities, large U.S. cylinders for straight highways and super sports cars with exotic twists on the very technical lines for example on the lace roads in the mountains.
And the challenge mode, which are races in particular places you know about the adventure, goes very well with the main regimen of the story.
Not only do you receive medals but also experience points that add to your profile that is common to challenges and adventure.
When you have reached the highest level of driver, different objects begin to unlock:
It connects online with the Autolog feature which, among other things, compares your results with those of other players and provides you with other features in the community.
One of the most difficult shots to understand is the situation of the last race of the adventure.
You arrive with your car in the subway tunnel (it looks like) where you drive in the dark on the roads (it looks like).
Your speed indicator shows you between 150 and 200 km/h (previously) and behind you comes a subway branch that sends the car directly to the railroad.
At the editorial office we had a discussion for a few days about whether someone really thought about creating this game or whether the authors really take us for fools.
The technical part of the game is not extra, but the visual part is generally pleasant and in some cases really great.
What is disturbing is that in more extreme situations, the imagery does not hold the level and in some cases tragically.
This is especially true of accidents with a large number of participants when fluid imaging is no longer useful to you.
The sound part is good and the track is the choice.
In order to please as many and especially the most young audience a new soundtrack was created in the style "I mix everything", but one can expect that no one will buy the game for music.
The general impression of Need for Speed: Le Run is therefore really confusing.
If the game didn’t have those stupid mistakes we could say without fear that it’s the best production of NFS in recent years.
But this game gives the impression of not being finished.
The fun is really good but prepare yourself for the mistakes to get in your eyes with the power of an aerodrome reflector.
The students of velvet in concert with the choirs of Charles University
The Festa Academica festival offers for the third time festivities that connect the International Student Day with the anniversary of the Velvet Revolution with a musical part.
During the festival there are 20 choirs from high schools and secondary classes.
The highlight of the festival is two concerts organized on November 17.
"Charles University has an important part in this festival."
“Among the choirs there is the Choeur of the Faculty of Pedagogy and Humanities, in the committee of the festival is the rector Vaclav Hampl,” says the head of the organizing team Jakub Calou.
The highlight of the festival is the Choeur des lycées and secondary classes concert which takes place with free entrance on 17 November from 14 hours on the space located in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
In the program there is the composition of the well-known Czech jazzman Karel Ruzicka, Celebration Jazz mass.
In the evening, the concert "Velour Students" takes place in the premises of the National House in Vinohrady, during which the choirs of the higher schools as well as that of Charles University take place.
The aim of the Festa Academica is not only to celebrate with dignity the International Day of Students and to commemorate the 22nd anniversary of the Velvet Revolution, but also to present to the public a music of choir of the highest level and to develop the creative cooperation of young people.
The main organizer is the Union of Czech Choirs in cooperation with the high school Jan Kepler.
All the action is placed under the aegis of Bohuslav Svoboda, Mayor of Prague and Vaclav Hampl, Rector of Charles University.
The festival takes place from 16 to 20 November in Prague and Pardubice.
The program also offers high-level concerts, musical meetings, student happenings and other activities.
Those interested will find all the information on the web pages of the festival www.festaacademica.cz.
