Thus was the work of the person of Cali who identified the body of Alfonso Cano
A dactyloscope of Cali has gone down in history as the man who confirmed the death of Alfonso Cano.
The work of these officials is crucial.
On November 4, a CTI dactyloscope specialist from Cali went down in history as the person who confirmed the identity of the Farc's supreme leader: "Alfonso Cano", confronting his fingerprints.
Of the seven dactyloscopes working in the local offices of the CTI, this week was the “availability” tour of Eliasar Gonz<0xC3><0xA1>lez, a Puerto Tejada man who has been working in the field of judicial investigation for 21 years.
At the beginning of his career, Gonz<0xC3><0xA1>lez worked in the municipalities of Choc<0xC3><0xB3>, where many times he had to spend more than five days in the forest to get to the place where the bodies were to be identified.
In the year 2000 he moved to the capital of Valle and after taking adequate courses, he specialized in dactyloscopy, which is the study of the skin of friction, i.e. the palms and feet.
During the week of the operation against the alias Alfonso Cano, Elijah was warned to take clothes with him for at least three days.
Something very big was waiting for him.
On Friday night he left for Cauca in a Palmira helicopter.
He knew that he had to identify two bodies and that it was suspected that one of them was that of the man who was leading the world’s oldest guerrilla, so he was asked to take the card with the ten fingerprints of Guillermo Le<0xC3><0xB3>n S<0xC3><0xA1>enz (his real name).
But when he arrived with the investigation team at the body site, he did not recognize him by his physical appearance, because he was very different from what he had seen in the media.
He had no beard, he was dressed like a peasant in the area, without glasses and much thinner.
But the prints don't lie.
Accompanied by a galtonian magnifying glass, ink, a pick-up and a lantern, Eleazar compared the digital footprints of the corpse with those of the map.
His eye did not deceive him: it was "Alfonso Cano".
That same night, the man from Puerto Tejada was the head who confirmed to the Minister of Defense, Juan Carlos Pinz<0xC3><0xB3>n that yes, he was the supreme leader of the Farc.
In search of the imprint
For a Sij<0xC3><0xAD>n de Cali dactyloscoper, the recognition that President Juan Manuel Santos made to Eliasar Gonz<0xC3><0xA1>lez, in a press conference for the operation against "Cano", is very significant.
A lot of people don't know our work.
Dactyloscopy is an exact science, with no margin of error, which can be crucial in solving crimes.
Apart from identifying the bodies, dactyloscopicists support investigations into crimes such as theft and murder and confirm the identity of the captured persons.
When captured, many criminals present false identity cards or do not have documents.
We take their fingerprints and search them in the database.
The researcher said that in a case of theft he had to remove a part of the wall from a house, because in this place the thief had pressed his hand to get out a safe full of jewelry and money.
“The walls are difficult because they are not adequate surfaces to pull a digital footprint, but in this case we were able to get the full hand print and identify the offender who had participated in different flights,” he recalls.
Imprints may also disprove or confirm suspects in homicide cases.
Recently, a dead man was found with bottles of liquor around him.
Through the investigation it was determined that a parent might be suspected of the crime and indeed a print on the bottle coincided.
Even if it doesn't guarantee he's the killer, it puts him on the crime scene.
A CTI dactyloscope expert explained that “the fingerprints of objects with chemical or physical reagents” were extracted.
When they appear, a pick-up or strip is used to pick them up.
Subsequently, the fingerprints are sent to Asif, the declension database, or to the National Civil Registry.
“The problem is that there are still a lot of Colombians without papers,” said the CTI expert.
He explained that not everything is as shown in the CSI television program.
As everything that shines is not gold, everything that you touch does not necessarily become an imprint.
However, it can be used if the necessary confrontation is carried out.
